Period, birth, death, inspiriation, convert, fact, when is feast day

Saint Francis of Assisi

Saint Francis of Assisi was a saint in the period of the church of triumphant in 11th century. He was born in 1181 or 1182. He died on his feast day of October 3 in the year 1226. He was baptised when he was an infant and was raised as a christian. Saint Francis founded Franciscan orders. 

Saint Elizabeth Ann Seton was a saint of the Resaissance or the Missionary church and was born August 28 1774 and was the first American born saint. She died on her feast day of January 4 in 1821. She grew up as a Christian. She opened a Catholic School: Saint Mary's. 


